{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"UTyVZZrIY615EpsVASnyB","title":"Dongle","desc":"","updated":1652510133044,"created":1644056764210,"custom":{},"fname":"ee.nrf52840.dongle","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"febffefe04b228cb028ffbdf02717e3a","links":[{"type":"wiki","from":{"fname":"ee.nrf52840.dongle","id":"UTyVZZrIY615EpsVASnyB","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"ee.zephyr","alias":"ee.zephyr","position":{"start":{"line":35,"column":1,"offset":807},"end":{"line":35,"column":14,"offset":820},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"ee.zephyr"}},{"type":"ref","from":{"fname":"ee.nrf52840.dongle","id":"UTyVZZrIY615EpsVASnyB","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"ee.nrfutil","position":{"start":{"line":42,"column":1,"offset":1181},"end":{"line":42,"column":28,"offset":1208},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"ee.nrfutil","anchorHeader":"usage"}},{"from":{"fname":"proj.zb-home-automation","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":4,"column":3,"offset":13},"end":{"line":4,"column":25,"offset":35},"indent":[]},"value":"ee.nrf52840.dongle","alias":"ee.nrf52840.dongle"},{"from":{"fname":"proj.zb-home-automation","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":22,"column":23,"offset":1265},"end":{"line":22,"column":45,"offset":1287},"indent":[]},"value":"ee.nrf52840.dongle","alias":"ee.nrf52840.dongle"},{"from":{"fname":"ee.nrf-connect-sdk.zb","vaultName":"vault"},"type":"backlink","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":25,"offset":743},"end":{"line":16,"column":47,"offset":765},"indent":[]},"value":"ee.nrf52840.dongle","alias":"ee.nrf52840.dongle"}],"anchors":{"datasheet":{"type":"header","text":"Datasheet","value":"datasheet","line":8,"column":0,"depth":2},"pinout":{"type":"header","text":"Pinout","value":"pinout","line":12,"column":0,"depth":2},"layout":{"type":"header","text":"Layout","value":"layout","line":16,"column":0,"depth":2},"buttons-and-leds":{"type":"header","text":"Buttons and LEDs","value":"buttons-and-leds","line":20,"column":0,"depth":2},"zephyr-docs":{"type":"header","text":"Zephyr Docs","value":"zephyr-docs","line":39,"column":0,"depth":2},"programming-the-dongle":{"type":"header","text":"Programming the dongle","value":"programming-the-dongle","line":44,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"kWFdZQuRbvz7uwXfqCA8n","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"dongle\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#dongle\"></a>Dongle</h1>\n<h2 id=\"datasheet\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#datasheet\"></a>Datasheet</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://infocenter.nordicsemi.com/pdf/nRF52840_Dongle_User_Guide_v1.0.pdf\">https://infocenter.nordicsemi.com/pdf/nRF52840_Dongle_User_Guide_v1.0.pdf</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"pinout\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#pinout\"></a>Pinout</h2>\n<p><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-02-05-20-26-18.png\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"layout\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#layout\"></a>Layout</h2>\n<p><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-02-10-21-40-45.png\"></p>\n<h2 id=\"buttons-and-leds\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#buttons-and-leds\"></a>Buttons and LEDs</h2>\n<p><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-02-10-21-33-13.png\"></p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<table><thead><tr><th>Part</th><th>Description</th><th>GPIO</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>SW1</td><td>Button</td><td>P1.06</td></tr><tr><td>SW2</td><td>Reset</td><td>P0.18 (1)</td></tr><tr><td>LD1</td><td>Green</td><td>P0.06</td></tr><tr><td>LD2</td><td>Red</td><td>P0.08</td></tr><tr><td>LD2</td><td>Green</td><td>P1.09</td></tr><tr><td>LD2</td><td>Blue</td><td>P0.12</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<ul>\n<li>What do the GPIO numbers mean?</li>\n</ul>\n<blockquote>\n<p>1) SW2 is also connected to P0.19, P0.21, P0.23, and P0.25. This is done to simplify PCB routing. These\nGPIOs should not be used and should be left as input with no pull or be disconnected by firmware.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"zephyr-docs\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#zephyr-docs\"></a>Zephyr Docs</h2>\n<p><a href=\"/notes/notes/qoWNfMZ0oqJ0T3ag3HFaR\">Zephyr</a>\n<a href=\"https://developer.nordicsemi.com/nRF_Connect_SDK/doc/latest/zephyr/boards/arm/nrf52840dongle_nrf52840/doc/index.html\">nRF52840 Dongle - Zephyr Project Documentation</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"programming-the-dongle\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#programming-the-dongle\"></a>Programming the dongle</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://jimmywongiot.com/2019/10/25/how-to-use-the-nrf52840-dongle-pca10059-as-development-board/\">How to use the NRF52840 Dongle (PCA10059) as development board</a></p>\n<p></p><p></p><div class=\"portal-container\">\n<div class=\"portal-head\">\n<div class=\"portal-backlink\">\n<div class=\"portal-title\">From <span class=\"portal-text-title\">Nrfutil</span></div>\n<a href=\"/notes/notes/4hqUGCEUyFhWBqlocNhLF\" class=\"portal-arrow\">Go to text <span class=\"right-arrow\">→</span></a>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"portal-parent-anchor\" class=\"portal-parent\" markdown=\"1\">\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-top\"></div>\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-bottom\"></div><h2 id=\"usage\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#usage\"></a>Usage</h2>\n<p>Example of usage with thread which is applicable to <a href=\"/notes/notes/oMZ0UCDQcTWH0WcIN0Dpc\">ZigBee</a></p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Reset the board into the Nordic bootloader by pressing the RESET button.</p>\n<p><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-02-18-21-36-10.png\" alt=\"Dongle PCB\"></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Compile a Zephyr application; we’ll use blinky.</p>\n<pre class=\"language-batch\"><code class=\"language-batch\"><span class=\"token command\"><span class=\"token keyword\">west</span> build <span class=\"token parameter attr-name\">-b</span> nrf52840dongle_nrf52840 zephyr/samples/basic<span class=\"token parameter attr-name\">/blinky</span></span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Package the application for the bootloader using nrfutil:</p>\n<pre class=\"language-batch\"><code class=\"language-batch\"><span class=\"token command\"><span class=\"token keyword\">nrfutil</span> pkg generate <span class=\"token parameter attr-name\">--hw-version</span> <span class=\"token number\">52</span> <span class=\"token parameter attr-name\">--sd-req</span>=0x00 \\</span>\n        --application build/zephyr/zephyr.hex \\\n        --application-version 1 blinky.zip\n</code></pre>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n<table><thead><tr><th>Flag</th><th>Description</th><th>Mandatory</th></tr></thead><tbody><tr><td><code>--hw-version 52</code></td><td>Hardware version indicating this build is for the dongle</td><td>Yes</td></tr><tr><td><code>--sd-req=0x00</code></td><td>Presumably this indicates no soft device is required</td><td>Yes</td></tr><tr><td><code>--application build/zephyr/zephyr.hex</code></td><td><code>.hex</code> file to be packaged`</td><td>Yes</td></tr><tr><td><code>--application-version 1</code></td><td>App version</td><td>No</td></tr></tbody></table>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Flash it onto the board. Note /dev/ttyACM0 is for Linux; it will be something like COMx on Windows, and something else on macOS.</p>\n<pre class=\"language-batch\"><code class=\"language-batch\"><span class=\"token command\"><span class=\"token keyword\">nrfutil</span> dfu usb-serial -pkg blinky.zip <span class=\"token parameter attr-name\">-p</span> /dev/ttyACM0</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Source:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.nordicsemi.com/nRF_Connect_SDK/doc/latest/zephyr/boards/arm/nrf52840dongle_nrf52840/doc/index.html?highlight=nrfutil#option-1-using-the-built-in-bootloader-only\">nRF52840 Dongle - Zephyr Project Documentation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://developer.nordicsemi.com/nRF_Connect_SDK/doc/latest/nrf/ug_thread_tools.html?highlight=nrfutil\">Thread tools - nRF Connect SDK 1.9.99 documentation</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"troubleshooting\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#troubleshooting\"></a>Troubleshooting</h2>\n<h3 id=\"no-moduled-named-constants\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#no-moduled-named-constants\"></a>No moduled named 'constants'</h3>\n<blockquote>\n<p>ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'constants'</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://devzone.nordicsemi.com/f/nordic-q-a/65889/nrfutil-modulenotfounderror-no-module-named-constants\">nrfutil ModuleNotFoundError: No module named constants - Nordic Q&#x26;A - Nordic DevZone - Nordic DevZone</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Python 3.8.6 seems to be a compatible version</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Solution</strong>: install using python 3.8 with <a href=\"/notes/notes/UN5ygEfGQgASMxZdZ2426\">Py Launcher</a></p>\n<pre class=\"language-batch\"><code class=\"language-batch\"><span class=\"token command\"><span class=\"token keyword\">py</span> <span class=\"token number\">-3</span>.<span class=\"token number\">8</span> <span class=\"token parameter attr-name\">-m</span> pip install nrfutil</span>\n</code></pre>\n<p>Reference:</p>\n<p></p><p></p><div class=\"portal-container\">\n<div class=\"portal-head\">\n<div class=\"portal-backlink\">\n<div class=\"portal-title\">From <span class=\"portal-text-title\">Py Launcher</span></div>\n<a href=\"/notes/notes/UN5ygEfGQgASMxZdZ2426\" class=\"portal-arrow\">Go to text <span class=\"right-arrow\">→</span></a>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"portal-parent-anchor\" class=\"portal-parent\" markdown=\"1\">\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-top\"></div>\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-bottom\"></div><h2 id=\"use-a-commmand-with-a-specific-version-eg-pip\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#use-a-commmand-with-a-specific-version-eg-pip\"></a>Use a commmand with a specific version e.g. pip</h2>\n<pre class=\"language-batch\"><code class=\"language-batch\"><span class=\"token command\"><span class=\"token keyword\">py</span> <span class=\"token number\">-3</span>.<span class=\"token number\">9</span> <span class=\"token parameter attr-name\">-m</span> pip freeze</span>\n</code></pre>\n<h2 id=\"set-an-alias\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#set-an-alias\"></a>Set an alias</h2>\n<pre class=\"language-ps1\"><code class=\"language-ps1\">Set-Alias -Name &#x3C;new_command_name> -Value python3\n</code></pre></div></div><p></p><p></p>\n<h2 id=\"notes\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#notes\"></a>Notes</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Soft devices must be included <a href=\"https://infocenter.nordicsemi.com/topic/ug_gsg_ses/UG/gsg/softdevices.html\">Overview of SoftDevices for the nRF5 Series</a>\n<ul>\n<li>Is there one for ZigBee?\n<ul>\n<li>There does not appear to be one for ZigBee, rather the ZBOSS binary is included in the build?</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><p></p><p></p>\n<hr>\n<strong>Backlinks</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/notes/vn4QH8axQkezeOvv8cSG5\">ZigBee Home Automation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/notes/notes/oMZ0UCDQcTWH0WcIN0Dpc\">ZigBee</a></li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"wn8PE1RhG0znK1alrGFYv","title":"Welcome","desc":"","updated":1647739693733,"created":1631901573363,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":"vault"},"contentHash":"25f6a870234e6662373e3b363ac6e7ff","links":[],"anchors":{},"children":["9nbHM9DXYJiw0wOL5EHqu","49nbdlbyhuggwhb17c4ckrc","etnjoq40t5e9gp3i9i0ebg4","SEWMNyq5ejB4Uu2o5gD1F","30970790-4080-4f49-a9e6-d3ea9f8a2f5e","oGtULAvsKCL7IqVaNh9x5","kxlbgahdm89suj3rh234zd2","haa2RJrh1FmtvgDrCgMuO","sHUgvR09969GI1KByYETE","6y2lfHzDgTsk4Jrl7vL24","D6TMhnzbxXgM6H69SHyDd","9itq04txzxzb62nmstlovti","4nqbPU2WajRDXAXqSDnwo","5acd228c-faa2-4c6c-8fed-6abd55a1e819","2pquOIrwpkRIflevQW2UU","fe3d08bb-d